descript.abstract: Police stations, generated by PBS&J for HAZUS analysis input needs. PBS&J stated (7/19/2006) in general QA/QC: "Roughly accurate to +/- 500 ft versus DOQQ."Clipped to the Primary/Secondary Delta by David Forc Consulting Engineers (2013)
descript.purpose: This data is used to estimate the damage (and resulting loss of functionality) associated with police station Facilities for a given flood, hurricane, and/or earthquake scenario.
descript.supplinf: Dataset obtained by DWR Delta-Suisun Marsh Office by PBS&J Corp in 6/2006.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data is used to estimate the damage (and resulting loss of functionality) associated with police station Facilities for a given flood, hurricane, and/or earthquake scenario.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Police stations, generated by PBS&J for HAZUS analysis input needs. PBS&J stated (7/19/2006) in general QA/QC: "Roughly accurate to +/- 500 ft versus DOQQ."

Clipped to the Primary/Secondary Delta.

Oakley, Pittsburg, and Antioch stations added 11/05/2019.
